---
import TradeHubLayout from '../layouts/TradeHubLayout.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "How does the AI handle plumbing-specific calls?",
    answer: "Your AI receptionist is trained with plumbing vocabulary — it understands the difference between a boiler service and a boiler breakdown, a dripping tap and a burst pipe, a blocked drain and a collapsed sewer line. When a customer calls, it captures the job type, location, urgency, and contact details. For emergencies like burst pipes, gas leaks, or flooding, it escalates immediately."
  },
  {
    question: "Can the AI tell the difference between an emergency and a routine job?",
    answer: "Yes. The AI is specifically trained to identify plumbing emergencies — burst pipes, major leaks, no hot water with a vulnerable person in the property, gas-related smells near a boiler. When it detects an emergency, it escalates the call directly to your mobile. If you're unreachable, our human operators step in. Routine jobs — like a dripping tap, a toilet that won't flush, or a radiator not heating — are captured and sent to you to action when you're free."
  },
  {
    question: "I'm a sole trader — is this worth it for a one-man band?",
    answer: "Sole traders are exactly who this is built for. You're the one under the sink, on the boiler, or in the loft — and you're the one missing calls because of it. Research shows that 62% of calls to trade businesses go unanswered. If just one missed call a month costs you a £200 boiler service, that's £2,400 a year lost. At £99/month, this pays for itself the very first time it captures a job you would've missed."
  },
  {
    question: "Does the AI give quotes or book appointments?",
    answer: "No — and deliberately. The AI never provides quotes, diagnoses faults, or books appointments. Those are decisions only you should make. It captures the customer's details, understands the nature of the job, assesses urgency, and sends everything to you. You stay in control of your diary and your pricing."
  },
  {
    question: "What about Gas Safe requirements — does the AI handle that?",
    answer: "The AI doesn't discuss Gas Safe registration or provide technical advice — those are regulated conversations that need a qualified person. What it does is capture the job details accurately. If someone calls about a boiler installation, the AI logs it as a boiler install enquiry and includes all the details. You handle the technical and regulatory discussion when you call the customer back."
  },
  {
    question: "How quickly will I receive the lead details?",
    answer: "Instantly. The moment a call ends or a message is received, you get a notification with the full details — customer name, phone number, location, job type, urgency assessment, and any notes. You can receive these via SMS, email, or through the Rapid Receptionist dashboard. There's no delay — your leads are sent in real-time."
  },
  {
    question: "What if I only do certain types of plumbing work?",
    answer: "We configure the AI specifically for your services. If you only do boilers and heating, the AI knows not to accept general plumbing enquiries. If you specialise in bathrooms, it focuses on those. If you do emergency callouts but not installations, it's set up accordingly. The AI represents your business exactly the way you'd want a receptionist to."
  },
  {
    question: "I already have a website — does this replace it?",
    answer: "No. Rapid Receptionist works alongside your existing website. We add a chat widget to your site that lets visitors speak directly to your AI receptionist. Your website stays exactly as it is — we just add another way for customers to reach you and get an instant response, even when you're on a job."
  }
];
---

<TradeHubLayout
  title="AI Receptionist for UK Plumbers — Never Miss a Job | Rapid Receptionist"
  description="AI receptionist built for UK plumbers. Answers calls, WhatsApp, SMS & 6 more channels 24/7. Knows your trade. Only £99/mo. 30-day money-back guarantee."
  canonicalUrl="/ai-receptionist-for-plumbers/"
  tradeName="Plumber"
  tradeNamePlural="Plumbers"
  tradeSlug="plumbers"
  headline="The AI Receptionist Built for UK Plumbers. Never Miss a Job."
  accentWord="UK Plumbers"
  subhead="You're under the sink, on the boiler, or knee-deep in a cylinder cupboard. Your AI receptionist answers every call, captures every lead, and escalates emergencies — so you never lose a job because you couldn't get to the phone."
  speedStat="78% of customers hire the first plumber to respond."
  speedText="When someone's got a burst pipe at 11pm or a boiler that's packed in on a Sunday morning, they're not waiting around. They're calling the next plumber on the list. Rapid Receptionist makes sure you're always first."
  scenario="It's 7:30am on a Monday. You're halfway through a boiler install in Croydon when your phone starts buzzing. A homeowner in Bromley has a leak under the kitchen sink — water's spreading. A letting agent in Lewisham needs an emergency plumber for a tenant's burst pipe. A customer you quoted last week wants to go ahead with a bathroom refit. You can't answer any of them — your hands are full of copper pipe and flux. Without Rapid Receptionist, those three leads call the next plumber on Google. With it, every single one is answered instantly, details captured, and emergencies flagged to you immediately."
  faqs={faqs}
/>
